@page "/"

<PageTitle>EF Core Essentials &mdash; .NET 10</PageTitle>

<div class="dc-hero">
    <div class="dc-hero-inner">
        <div class="dc-hero-eyebrow">
            <span class="dc-hero-badge">DC</span>
            DigitalCreation &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; LIA 2025
        </div>
        <h1 class="dc-hero-title">Entity Framework Core</h1>
        <p class="dc-hero-sub">
            Best practices &mdash; no Repository pattern, no overhead.
        </p>
        <div class="dc-hero-actions">
            <a href="/products" class="btn btn-primary px-4">Products Demo</a>
            <a href="/presentation" class="btn btn-outline-primary px-4">&#9654;&nbsp; Open Presentation</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container-xl px-4 py-5">
    <div class="row g-4">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-header d-flex align-items-center gap-2">
                    <span class="dc-tag dc-tag--green">Included Patterns</span>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <ul class="dc-list">
                        <li><code>IEntityTypeConfiguration</code> &mdash; clean entity config</li>
                        <li><code>ISoftDelete</code> &mdash; automatic soft-delete in <code>SaveChangesAsync</code></li>
                        <li><code>IAuditable</code> &mdash; <code>CreatedBy / UpdatedBy</code> auto-stamps</li>
                        <li><code>IHaveSiteId</code> &mdash; compiler-enforced multi-tenant filters</li>
                        <li><code>PriceWithCurrency</code> &mdash; value object with <code>[Owned]</code></li>
                        <li>JSON columns via <code>OwnsOne / OwnsMany</code></li>
                        <li>Compiled queries via <code>EF.CompileAsyncQuery</code></li>
                        <li>Reusable pagination with <code>ToPagingAsync&lt;T&gt;()</code></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-header d-flex align-items-center gap-2">
                    <span class="dc-tag dc-tag--accent">Best Practices</span>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <ul class="dc-list">
                        <li>Always <code>.Select()</code> on list queries &mdash; never over-fetch</li>
                        <li>Extension methods on <code>IQueryable&lt;T&gt;</code> instead of Repository</li>
                        <li>Interface-driven global query filters &mdash; compiler enforced</li>
                        <li><code>.AsNoTracking()</code> for all read-only queries</li>
                        <li><code>ExecuteUpdateAsync / ExecuteDeleteAsync</code> for bulk ops</li>
                        <li><code>AsAsyncEnumerable</code> for streaming large result sets</li>
                        <li><code>TagWith()</code> to label queries in logs &amp; traces</li>
                        <li>Optimized EF Core &asymp; Dapper &asymp; ADO.NET throughput</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dc-notice mt-4">
        <strong>Don&apos;t wrap <code>DbContext</code> in a Repository.</strong>
        <code>DbContext</code> already is the repository and unit of work.
        A wrapper layer re-invents <code>DbSet&lt;T&gt;</code>, loses <code>IQueryable</code> composability,
        and adds zero value. Use extension methods on <code>IQueryable&lt;T&gt;</code> instead.
    </div>
</div>
